solution.p:
First, we divide both sides by C to isolate the power.
		b^{kt} = \dfrac{P}{C}
Then we write the exponential equation in logarithmic form:
		 kt \amp = \log_b {\dfrac{P}{C}} \amp\amp \glert{\text{Divide both sides by}~k.}
			t  \amp = \dfrac{1}{k}\log_b {\dfrac{P}{C}}

